# AMR-GigaWord 200k

# ::id 0 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok china has rejected us demands that it beef up legislation to halt the piracy of us goods , branding them a `` flagrant intervention in china 's sovereign rights and its internal affairs , '' a report said thursday .
# ::alignments
(s / say-01
      :ARG0 (r / report)
      :ARG1 (r2 / reject-01
            :ARG0 (c / country
                  :name (n / name
                        :op1 "China"))
            :ARG1 (d / demand-01
                  :ARG0 c
                  :ARG1 (b / beef-up-01
                        :ARG0 c
                        :ARG1 (l / legislate-01)
                        :purpose (h / halt-01
                              :ARG0 c
                              :ARG1 (p / piracy
                                    :mod (g / good
                                          :poss c)))))
            :ARG1-of (c2 / cause-01
                  :ARG0 (b2 / brand-01
                        :ARG0 c
                        :ARG1 l
                        :ARG2 (ii / intervene-01
                              :ARG0 l
                              :ARG1 (a / and
                                    :op1 (r3 / right-05
                                          :ARG1 c
                                          :mod (s2 / sovereign))
                                    :op2 (a2 / affair-02
                                          :ARG1 c
                                          :ARG1-of (ii2 / internal-02)))
                              :manner (f / flagrant)))))
      :time (d2 / date-entity
            :weekday (t / thursday)))

# ::id 1 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok `` why spend $ ### million on a film when you can pick up a low-budget flick for peanuts _ and make a fortune ? '' goes the thinking in hollywood today .
# ::alignments
(g / go-06
      :ARG0 (t / think-01
            :location (m / market-sector
                  :name (n / name
                        :op1 "Hollywood")))
      :ARG1 (s / spend-01
            :ARG1 (f / film)
            :ARG3 (m2 / monetary-quantity
                  :quant 10000000
                  :unit (d / dollar))
            :ARG1-of (c / cause-01
                  :ARG0 (a / amr-unknown))
            :condition (p / possible-01
                  :ARG1 (a2 / and
                        :op1 (p2 / pick-up-04
                              :ARG0 (y / you)
                              :ARG1 (f2 / flick
                                    :ARG1-of (b / budget-01
                                          :ARG1-of (l / low-04)))
                              :ARG3 (p3 / peanut))
                        :op2 (m3 / make-05
                              :ARG0 y
                              :ARG1 (f3 / fortune)))))
      :time (t2 / today))

# ::id 2 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok america 's trade deficit surged to an all-time high of $ ###.# billion last year , nearly one-third larger than the previous record , reflecting a flood of imports ranging from foreign cars to oil and industrial machinery .
# ::alignments
(s / surge-01
      :ARG1 (d / deficit
            :mod (t / trade-01)
            :poss (c / country
                  :name (n / name
                        :op1 "America")))
      :ARG4 (m / monetary-quantity
            :quant 1000000000
            :unit (d2 / dollar)
            :ARG1-of (h / have-degree-91
                  :ARG2 (l / large)
                  :ARG3 (m2 / more
                        :quant (n2 / nearly
                              :op1 "1/3"))
                  :ARG4 (r / record
                        :time (p / previous))))
      :time (y / year
            :mod (l2 / last))
      :ARG1-of (r2 / reflect-01
            :ARG2 (f / flood-01
                  :ARG2 (ii / import-01
                        :ARG1-of (r3 / range-01
                              :ARG3 (c2 / car
                                    :mod (f2 / foreign))
                              :ARG4 (a / and
                                    :op1 (o / oil)
                                    :op2 (m3 / machinery
                                          :mod (ii2 / industry))))))))

                  :unit (d2 / dollar))

                  :weekday (w / wednesday))))

            :ARG1 (v / volume
                  :mod (t3 / trade-01))

                  :ARG2 (d2 / date-entity
                        :weekday (w / wednesday)))))

            :ARG0 (w / we)

                  :mod (s7 / space)

            :time (w2 / wednesday)))

# ::id 1939 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred

# ::alignments

                  :name (n / name

                        :op2 " securities"
                        :op3 "Co."))

            :ARG3 (m / most)
            :ARG5 (f2 / firm
                  :mod (s / securities)
                  :location (w / world)))
      :op2 (h2 / have-degree-91
            :ARG1 f
            :ARG2 (a2 / and
                  :op1 (s2 / sophisticated)
                  :op2 (p / powerful-02))
            :ARG3 (m2 / most)
            :ARG5 (f3 / firm
                  :location (c / country
                        :name (n2 / name
                              :op1 "Japan")))
            :mod (c2 / certain))
      :manner (m3 / measure-02
            :quant (s3 / some)))

# ::id 1940 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred

# ::alignments
(e / erupt-01
      :ARG1 (n / nightclub)
      :ARG2 (f / fire
            :ARG0-of (r / rage-02))
      :time (d / display-01
            :ARG1 (p / pyrotechnics)
            :location (c / concert
                  :mod (r2 / rock)))
      :ARG0-of (k / kill-01
            :ARG1 (p2 / person
                  :quant (a / at-least
                        :op1 100)))
      :ARG0-of (ii / injure-01
            :ARG1 (p3 / person
                  :ARG1-of (h / have-quant-91
                        :ARG3 (m / more)
                        :ARG4 (p4 / person
                              :mod (o / other)))))
      :time (r3 / rush-01
            :ARG1 (m2 / mob
                  :ARG0-of (f2 / frantic-00))
            :ARG2 (e2 / escape-01
                  :ARG0 m2)))

                              :op1 "Australia")))
            :time (d2 / date-entity
                  :weekday (m / monday))
            :ARG1-of (c3 / cause-01
                  :ARG0 (a / and
                        :op1 (g / go-08
                              :ARG1 (a2 / and
                                    :op1 (c4 / company
                                          :name (n2 / name
                                                :op1 "News"
                                                :op2 "Corporation")
                                          :mod (h / heavy)
                                          :mod (m2 / market))
                                    :op2 (c5 / company
                                          :name (n3 / name
                                                :op1 "Telstra")
                                          :mod h))
                              :ARG2 (d3 / dividend
                                    :time (e / ex)))
                        :op2 (l / lose-02
                              :ARG0 (s3 / sector
                                    :mod (r / resource))
                              :ARG1 (g2 / ground))))))

            :mod (l / level
                  :mod (j / junior)))
      :time (d / date-entity
            :weekday (t / thursday))
      :location (c / county
            :name (n2 / name
                  :op1 "Kaohsiung"))
      :location (ii / in-front-of
            :op1 (p / person
                  :ARG0-of (s / scout-01)
                  :source (b / baseball
                        :mod (l2 / league
                              :ARG1-of (m / major-02)))
                  :quant (m2 / multiple
                        :op1 20))))
